<subSubSection id="C36165495E31FF919E85F99EFD3D9E7A" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC436C25E31FF919E85F99EFD3D9E7A" blockId="8.[166,1224,1537,1628]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D415E31FF919F01F99EFE3F9E3D" authorityName="Leach &amp; Brewster" authorityYear="1815" box="[351,461,1537,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Chrysopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90FEAD05E31FF919F01F99EFE3F9E3D" box="[351,461,1537,1563]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Chrysopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes 50 species, occurring in the Holarctic Region (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B335E31FF919A2DF99EFF109E1A" author="Holzel, H." pageId="8" pageNumber="109" pagination="61 - 68" refId="ref6442" refString="Holzel, H. 1984. Chrysopidae of the Palearctic Region - a review'. In: Gepps, J., Aspock, H. and Holzel, H., eds. Progress in World's Neuropterology. Graz, 61 - 68. URL: http: // www. zobodat. at / pdf / MONO-ENT- NEURO _ MEN 1 _ 0061 - 0068. pdf." type="book chapter" year="1984">Hölzel, 1984</bibRefCitation>
), with 18 of them recorded in Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B335E31FF919CEFF9BEFCA09E1A" author="Letardi, A. &amp; Aspoeck, U. &amp; Aspoeck., H." box="[689,850,1569,1596]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" refId="ref6568" refString="Letardi, A., Aspoeck, U. &amp; Aspoeck., H. (2017). Fauna Europaea: Chrysopa. Chrysopidae. Neuroptera. Fauna Europaea version 2017.06. https: // fauna-eu. org / cdm _ dataportal / taxon / 0 e 963 b 9 c- 67 bd- 4 d 1 f- 93 b 8 - 69 d 3 bd 81809 d" type="url" year="2017">Letardi, 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Twelve species are distributed in the Ukrainian Carpathians (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B335E31FF919C50F9DEFD319E7A" author="Serediuk, G. V." box="[526,707,1601,1628]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" pagination="46 - 68" refId="ref6696" refString="Serediuk, G. V. 2016. Neuropterida (Insecta. Neuroptera) of the Ukrainian Carpathians. Ukrainian Entomological Journal, 1 - 2 (11), 46 - 68." type="journal article" year="2016">Serediuk, 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
